node.text: Leading up to the Lousa World Cup in full race pace training and timing mode on some of my favourite trails (this one is called Memphis). Now that the first three world cups have been postponed or cancelled, I will be taking a short break from riding my bike at full speed to enjoy some lower impact activities that I enjoy as the world faces this challenge together. Please stay safe and do your part to stay socially distanced while medical professionals help those in need.

node.text:
Not the post I wanted to be making this weekend, but due to a hand injury I had to sit this weeks World Cup in Maribor out. I’m going to be working as hard as I can to come back as quickly as possible and hopefully be back for world championships! Thanks to the team @specializedgravity for another great weekend considering the circumstances and congratulations to @loicbruni29 for getting back on the box!! 

PC: Seb Scheick
